defs.docs: Epoch-based memory reclamation.

defs.name: Atomic
defs.docs: An atomic pointer that can be safely shared between threads.

defs.name: null
defs.docs: Returns a new null atomic pointer.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Allocates `value` on the heap and returns a new atomic pointer pointing to it.

defs.name: load
defs.value: fn <'g> (&self, ord: Ordering, _: &'g Guard) -> Shared<'g, T>
defs.docs: Loads a `Shared` from the atomic pointer.

defs.name: store
defs.value: fn <'g, P> (&self, new: P, ord: Ordering) -> ()
defs.docs: Stores a `Shared` or `Owned` pointer into the atomic pointer.

defs.name: swap
defs.value: fn <'g, P> (&self, new: P, ord: Ordering, _: &'g Guard) -> Shared<'g, T>
defs.docs:
Stores a `Shared` or `Owned` pointer into the atomic pointer, returning the previous
 `Shared`.

defs.name: compare_and_set
defs.value: fn <'g, O, P> (&self, current: Shared<T>, new: P, ord: O, _: &'g Guard) -> Result<Shared<'g, T>, CompareAndSetError<'g, T, P>>
defs.docs:
Stores the pointer `new` (either `Shared` or `Owned`) into the atomic pointer if the current
 value is the same as `current`. The tag is also taken into account, so two pointers to the
 same object, but with different tags, will not be considered equal.

defs.name: compare_and_set_weak
defs.value: fn <'g, O, P> (&self, current: Shared<T>, new: P, ord: O, _: &'g Guard) -> Result<Shared<'g, T>, CompareAndSetError<'g, T, P>>
defs.docs:
Stores the pointer `new` (either `Shared` or `Owned`) into the atomic pointer if the current
 value is the same as `current`. The tag is also taken into account, so two pointers to the
 same object, but with different tags, will not be considered equal.

defs.name: fetch_or

defs.name: fetch_xor
